e4d6b69a-736d-587c-bbed-7bd11276c3e1,tg:rubgr:1462,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"

[2 bladen] [blad 1, recto] Ad [Addendum] Sermon of St. John. Lucas Cranach, Fragment of a panel of this subject in Oldenburg Gemäldegalerie (H.W.[Herbert Wolfgang] KEISER, Gemäldegalerie Oldenburg (Catalogue, Munich 1966, p. 48) (probably right part) On the right people climbing a tree from which they watch and listen. By the right edge a potraitlike figure (trägt die Züge Friedrichs des Weisen?) c. 1510-16. 'Verwandt in der Komposition doch keineswegs übereinstimment mit dem Holzschnitt des gleichen Gegenstandes von 1516' Look up in Hollstein; [blad 2, recto] Ad Sermon of St John. Antwerp: Crédit Communal de Belge. L'Escaut et Anvers (Exh. 1966-67) [Max Servais, Frans Smekens, L' Escaut et Anvers : témoignages d'un essor, Anvers: Crédit communal, 1966], Pl. facing p. 24 of catalogue showing various preachers with crowds listening, and soldiers on guard. Anonymous woodcut inscribed at top: Antwerpen (central part only reproduced) Antwerp appears in background across the river. Open country with some trees. The crowd in the left background. Inscribed: Confessi. Below them in the wood a smaller crowd, with bearded preacher, inscribed: Walen. In centre larger crowd, also with bearded preacher inscribed: Reformeerd. In text p. 58 this woodcut is described as followed; [blad 2, verso] Anonyme. La rade d'Anvers - 1515(?) (in B. de Opitiis) Conciones reformatorum ac Martinistrarum extra Antwerpiam, 1566 (détail) Look up in BM.
